{
  "texts": [
    "As an interdisciplinary area, bioinformatics harnesses computer science, physics, biology, and mathematics [10,11].",
    "It is critical for data management in modern medicine and biology [12,13].",
    "Bioinformatics provides considerable support to deal with time context and cost issues in different tracks [14,15].",
    "Bioinformatics, as pertinent to genomics and genetics, is a scientific interdisciplinary field that utilizes computer technology to gather, store, evaluate, and distribute biological data, like DNA and amino acid sequences and annotations about them [16,17].Distributed computing is a versatile method that can be applied to a wide range of issues in bioinformatics.",
    "While it is commonly used for cost-efficiency in high-performance computing, in other domains, it has become a necessity [18]."
  ]
}